{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jkhu1N3TE3QLubzbzdSuqF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary with all the details:\n\n## Summary: Anchor-Client Package for E2E Testing\n\nI've found all the key information needed to use the anchor-client package for fetching on-chain accounts in E2E tests. Here's the complete guide:\n\n### Import Paths\n\n**Main exports from `@rng-utopia/anchor-client`:**\n```typescript\n// Location: /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts\n\n// IDL JSON (runtime)\nexport { CoinflipIDL, PlatformIDL };\n\n// Type definitions (compile-time)\nexport type { Coinflip, Platform };\n```\n\n### Program IDs\n\n**Coinflip Program:**\n```typescript\n// From game-engine: /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts\nimport { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"\n);\n\n// Also available from the IDL itself:\n// CoinflipIDL.address === \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"\n```\n\n**Platform Program:**\n```typescript\n// Hardcoded value in chain.ts (E2E example)\n\"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"\n\n// Also available from PlatformIDL:\n// PlatformIDL.address === \"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"\n```\n\n### Creating a Program Instance (Outside Bankrun)\n\n**Pattern from `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` (lines 64-72):**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\nimport { Connection } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\nfunction getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n  // Read-only provider (no wallet needed for queries)\n  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    connection,\n    {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],  // Empty wallet for read-only access\n    { commitment: \"confirmed\" }\n  );\n  return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n}\n```\n\n### Account Types & Fetching Patterns\n\n**Available Account Types:**\n\n| Program | Account Type | IDL Name | TypeScript Type |\n|---------|--------------|----------|-----------------|\n| Coinflip | Match account | `coinflipMatch` | `CoinflipMatch` |\n| Coinflip | Config account | `coinflipConfig` | `CoinflipConfig` |\n| Platform | Player profile | `playerProfile` | `PlayerProfile` |\n| Platform | Platform config | `platformConfig` | `PlatformConfig` |\n\n**Fetching Patterns (from chain.ts lines 185-302):**\n\n```typescript\n// 1. Fetch a single account by PDA\nconst program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\nconst [matchPda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n  [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer()],\n  COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n);\nconst match = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(matchPda);\n\n// 2. Fetch all accounts of a type (with optional filters)\nconst allMatches = await program.account.coinflipMatch.all();\n\n// 3. Fetch with memcmp filters (efficient on-chain filtering)\nconst matches = await program.account.coinflipMatch.all([\n  { memcmp: { offset: 8, bytes: playerBase58 } }  // Filter by creator\n]);\n\n// 4. Fetch config\nconst config = await program.account.coinflipConfig.fetch(configPda);\n```\n\n### Account Field Structure\n\n**CoinflipMatch account fields (from chain.ts lines 80-95):**\n```typescript\ninterface OnChainMatch {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;          // 0 = heads, 1 = tails\n  phase: RoundPhaseVariant;     // Enum: waiting|active|locked|resolving|settled|refunded\n  result: number;               // 0 or 1 (winning side)\n  winner: PublicKey;            // Pubkey::default() if not settled\n  claimed: boolean;\n  createdAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  resolveDeadline: { toNumber(): number };\n  vrfRequestKey: PublicKey;     // Orao randomness account address\n  bump: number;                 // PDA bump seed\n}\n```\n\n**CoinflipConfig account fields:**\n```typescript\n{\n  authority: PublicKey;\n  treasury: PublicKey;\n  paused: boolean;\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n**PlayerProfile account fields:**\n```typescript\n{\n  authority: PublicKey;         // Wallet that owns this profile\n  totalGames: number;           // (BN, call toNumber())\n  wins: number;                 // (BN, call toNumber())\n  totalWagered: number;         // lamports (BN, call toNumber())\n  totalWon: number;             // lamports (BN, call toNumber())\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\n### PDA Derivation Seeds\n\n**Coinflip Match:**\n```typescript\n[\"match\", creator.toBuffer()]\n```\n\n**Coinflip Config:**\n```typescript\n[\"coinflip_config\"]\n```\n\n**Player Profile:**\n```typescript\n[\"player_profile\", player.toBuffer()]\n```\n\n**Platform Config:**\n```typescript\n[\"platform_config\"]\n```\n\n### Key Files to Reference\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts` | Main exports (IDLs + types) |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json` | Coinflip IDL (929 lines, full ABI) |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/platform.json` | Platform IDL (337 lines, full ABI) |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts` | Program ID constants + PDA helpers |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` | Full production example of Program instantiation + account fetching |\n\n### Example E2E Test Pattern\n\n```typescript\nimport { Connection } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\nimport { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\nasync function testFetchMatch(rpcUrl: string) {\n  const connection = new Connection(rpcUrl);\n  \n  // Create program instance\n  const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n    connection,\n    {} as any,  // Empty wallet for read-only\n    { commitment: \"confirmed\" }\n  );\n  const program = new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n  \n  // Fetch all open matches\n  const matches = await program.account.coinflipMatch.all();\n  \n  // Process\n  matches.forEach(acc => {\n    const match = acc.account as any;\n    console.log(`Match ${acc.publicKey.toBase58()}`);\n    console.log(`  Creator: ${match.creator.toBase58()}`);\n    console.log(`  Phase: ${Object.keys(match.phase)[0]}`);\n  });\n}\n```\n\nAll the code paths and types needed for E2E integration are now clear and documented!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4b0db09fe1b079d4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60358\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 62722</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5c7393b1-80a9-4d3b-9693-3efb14711fd2","uuid":"f5ae7581-7921-49e2-8741-c25ea2c75c17","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how to use the anchor-client package for fetching on-chain accounts in E2E tests. Please find and read:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.ts` - the coinflip client\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/platform.ts` - the platform client\n3. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts` - main exports\n4. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/package.json` - package config\n\nAlso find the program IDs - search for where COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID and PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID are defined (likely in packages/anchor-client or in a config package).\n\nAlso check `sources/rng-utopia/packages/config/` for any program ID exports.\n\nI need to know:\n- How to cr