{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FxQcAAaDQaPqGTs9kbJZBt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QcF1s1wrKMiujg3Kmujnif","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/203-e2e-integration/spec.md","old_string":"- [ ] [test] Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates","new_string":"- [x] [test] Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates (done: iteration 6)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":216,"cache_read_input_tokens":68411,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":216},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5c7393b1-80a9-4d3b-9693-3efb14711fd2","uuid":"167a05e4-3106-43a2-85f2-9ff14068b285"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QcF1s1wrKMiujg3Kmujnif","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/203-e2e-integration/spec.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5c7393b1-80a9-4d3b-9693-3efb14711fd2","uuid":"ac2704a1-9850-414b-a5d7-e52188ee1a0e","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/203-e2e-integration/spec.md","oldString":"- [ ] [test] Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates","newString":"- [x] [test] Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates (done: iteration 6)","originalFile":"# Specification: 203 E2E Integration Tests\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P1 |\n| Phase | 2 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 5 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nEnd-to-end tests using Playwright that prove real transactions flow from the browser UI to on-chain programs and back. This spec defines two suites:\n\n1. **Local deterministic suite (`pnpm test:e2e`)** using `solana-test-validator` for fast CI gating.\n2. **Devnet real-provider suite (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`)** using deployed contracts and the real VRF provider.\n\nBoth suites use the TestWalletProvider (from spec 205) to inject test keypairs and sign real transactions without a browser extension.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a developer, I want an E2E test that runs the full coinflip lifecycle (create → join → resolve → claim) through the real UI so that I know the frontend and on-chain programs work together.\n- As a developer, I want E2E tests to catch regressions in the chain integration layer (chain.ts, CoinflipContext) that unit and component tests cannot.\n- As a CI system, I want deterministic headless local E2E tests so that pull requests are gated on integration correctness.\n- As a release system, I want real devnet + VRF E2E tests so that deployed contracts and provider callbacks are validated before release.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 9 (Quality & Testing)\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 2 — after wallet integration and component tests are stable\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — transaction builders\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — game state\n- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — on-chain program\n- `solana/programs/platform/` — on-chain program\n- `packages/wallet/src/` — TestWalletProvider (from spec 205)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- `solana/tests/coinflip.ts` — bankrun tests define expected on-chain behavior\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — UIMatch shape\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Local Deterministic Infrastructure\n\nSet up the deterministic local E2E environment with Playwright and a local Solana validator.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Playwright configured for E2E tests (separate from visual regression config)\n- [ ] Test setup script starts solana-test-validator with coinflip + platform programs deployed\n- [ ] Local suite deploys programs as part of setup (blank chain; no pre-deployed assumption)\n- [ ] Test setup airdrops SOL to test wallets\n- [ ] App starts with VITE_RPC_URL pointing to local validator\n- [ ] Test teardown stops the validator and cleans up\n- [ ] E2E test command: `pnpm test:e2e`\n\n### FR-2: Coinflip Full Lifecycle\n\nTest the complete coinflip flow through the UI.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Test wallet A connects, navigates to /coinflip, selects a tier, picks Heads, creates a match\n- [ ] Match appears in the open lobby\n- [ ] Test wallet B connects (second browser context), sees the match, joins it\n- [ ] Match transitions to locked phase in both contexts\n- [ ] Oracle resolves the match (direct RPC call in test, not through UI)\n- [ ] Winner sees \"You won\" result, loser sees \"You lost\"\n- [ ] Winner claims payout, balance increases by expected amount (pool minus 3% fee)\n- [ ] Match disappears from lobby after claim\n\n### FR-3: Cancel Flow\n\nTest match cancellation.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Creator creates a match, then cancels before anyone joins\n- [ ] Creator's balance is refunded (entry amount + rent)\n- [ ] Match disappears from the lobby\n- [ ] Creator can create a new match after cancellation\n\n### FR-4: Error Scenarios\n\nTest that error states surface correctly in the UI.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Creating a match with insufficient balance shows an error message\n- [ ] Joining an already-locked match shows an error message\n- [ ] Claiming as the loser shows an error message\n\n### FR-5: On-Chain State Verification\n\nLocal deterministic tests must verify on-chain state, not just UI state.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] After match creation, test queries the match PDA and verifies account data\n- [ ] After claim, test verifies the match account is closed\n- [ ] After claim, test verifies treasury received the fee\n- [ ] After claim, test verifies player profiles are updated (totalGames, wins)\n\n### FR-6: Devnet Real VRF Integration\n\nRun E2E tests against deployed devnet contracts and the real VRF provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Separate Playwright project/config for devnet suite (not sharing local validator setup)\n- [ ] App runs against devnet RPC with deployed coinflip/platform program IDs\n- [ ] Devnet suite does not deploy contracts; it fails fast if required deployed IDs/env are missing\n- [ ] Test triggers real VRF request path (no local mock resolve shortcut)\n- [ ] Test waits for real provider callback/fulfillment and asserts resolved winner/loser UI state\n- [ ] Winner claim succeeds and on-chain account/balance outcomes are verified on devnet\n- [ ] Test command: `pnpm test:e2e:devnet`\n- [ ] Suite includes retry/poll strategy and explicit timeout budget for async fulfillment\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Local lifecycle suite passes end-to-end in under 60 seconds\n- Local suite is deterministic (same result on every run)\n- Devnet suite passes against deployed contracts with real VRF fulfillment\n- No browser extension required (TestWalletProvider handles signing)\n- On-chain state matches expected values after each step in both suites\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Spec 205 (Real Wallet) — TestWalletProvider must exist\n- Spec 200 (Visual Regression) — Playwright already installed\n- solana-test-validator available in CI environment\n- Programs compiled and deployable (`anchor build`)\n- Devnet contracts deployed and environment variables documented for program IDs\n- Real VRF provider credentials/configuration available in devnet environment\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Two browser contexts simulate two different players\n- Local suite triggers resolution programmatically in tests (not through UI) for determinism\n- Devnet suite uses real VRF request/fulfillment path\n- Test validator starts fresh for each local test suite (clean state)\n- Airdrop is available on test validator (not rate-limited)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Local lifecycle passes | `pnpm test:e2e` output | Green local run |\n| 2 | Local on-chain state correct | Local RPC queries in test assertions | Account data matches |\n| 3 | Local deterministic | Run local suite 3 times consecutively | All pass |\n| 4 | Local under 60 seconds | Time local test run | Timing output |\n| 5 | Devnet VRF path passes | `pnpm test:e2e:devnet` output | Green devnet run |\n| 6 | Devnet fulfillment observed | Poll + assertion logs in test output | VRF callback evidence |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n- [x] [test] Baseline Playwright real-mode config and smoke spec exist (`playwright.real.config.ts`, `e2e/real/startup.spec.ts`) (done: prior specs)\n- [x] [test] Add dedicated local E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/local/**`) separated from visual and real-wallet smoke tests (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [test] Create localnet bootstrap script: start fresh `solana-test-validator`, deploy coinflip + platform programs, wait for RPC readiness (done: iteration 2)\n- [x] [test] Create localnet teardown script: stop validator process, clean temp ledger/logs, and guarantee cleanup on test failure (done: iteration 3)\n- [x] [test] Add deterministic wallet-funding helper (airdrop + confirm) for both test players before each local suite run (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [test] Add shared E2E helpers: selectors/page-object methods for create, join, claim, cancel, and reusable wait/assert primitives (done: iteration 5)\n- [ ] [test] Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates\n- [ ] [test] Add dual-browser-context fixture with isolated storage/session for player A and player B\n- [ ] [test] Implement local lifecycle test (create -> join -> resolve programmatically -> claim) with UI assertions in both contexts\n- [ ] [test] Implement local lifecycle on-chain assertions (match state after create, closed after claim, fee + profile invariants)\n- [ ] [test] Implement local cancel-flow test (create -> cancel -> refund verified -> lobby clears -> recreate works)\n- [ ] [test] Implement local error-flow tests (insufficient balance, join locked match, loser claim attempt)\n- [ ] [test] Add local suite command `pnpm test:e2e` that runs bootstrap -> tests -> teardown in one entrypoint\n- [ ] [test] Add devnet env contract (required vars + validation): RPC URL, coinflip/platform program IDs, VRF config; fail fast if missing\n- [ ] [test] Add dedicated devnet E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/devnet/**`) that does not run local bootstrap/deploy\n- [ ] [test] Implement devnet lifecycle test using deployed contracts + real VRF request/fulfillment path (no mock resolve shortcut)\n- [ ] [test] Add robust fulfillment polling/backoff + timeout budget in devnet test, with tx signature logging for failures\n- [ ] [test] Add devnet on-chain assertions for payout, fee transfer, and final match/account state\n- [ ] [test] Add devnet suite command `pnpm test:e2e:devnet` wired to the devnet project/config\n- [ ] [test] Prove local determinism by running `pnpm test:e2e` three consecutive times (all pass, stable assertions)\n- [ ] [test] Record local runtime evidence (<60s target) and devnet real-VRF pass evidence in test output artifacts/logs\n- [x] [test] Visual regression baseline updates are not required for this spec (test infra + assertions only; no intended UI redesign)\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] Local E2E tests pass (`pnpm test:e2e`)\n- [ ] Devnet E2E tests pass (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) in designated environment\n- [ ] No lint errors\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Local tests are deterministic (3 consecutive runs pass)\n- [ ] Devnet test demonstrates real VRF request-to-fulfillment path\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] N/A (E2E tests verify behavior, not appearance)\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No unhandled JS console errors during E2E runs\n- [ ] All RPC requests succeed\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n\n### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n\nAfter the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":175,"oldLines":7,"newStart":175,"newLines":7,"lines":[" - [x] [test] Create localnet teardown script: stop validator process, clean temp ledger/logs, and guarantee cleanup on test failure (done: iteration 3)"," - [x] [test] Add deterministic wallet-funding helper (airdrop + confirm) for both test players before each local suite run (done: iteration 4)"," - [x] [test] Add shared E2E helpers: selectors/page-object methods for create, join, claim, cancel, and reusable wait/assert primitives (done: iteration 5)","-- [ ] [test] Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates","+- [x] [test] Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates (done: iteration 6)"," - [ ] [test] Add dual-browser-context fixture with isolated storage/session for player A and player B"," - [ ] [test] Implement local lifecycle test (create -> join -> resolve programmatically -> claim) with UI assertions in both contexts"," - [ ] [test] Implement local lifecycle on-chain assertions (match state after create, closed after claim, fee + profile invariants)"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
